# Set the keys for the harness + provider you pick in the UI. You only need the
# ones for the combination you actually run; the server returns a clear error if a
# required key is missing for the selected combo. `local` runs on your host and
# uses your host CLI's own auth (no key needed).

# --- Harness keys (the in-sandbox coding-agent CLI authenticates with these) ---

# Claude Code → Anthropic. https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Codex → OpenAI. Injected into the sandbox AS CODEX_API_KEY (a bare OPENAI_API_KEY
# is accepted too and mapped to it). OpenCode also uses OPENAI_API_KEY.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# CODEX_API_KEY=

# Grok → xAI (GROK_API_KEY accepted as an alias).
# XAI_API_KEY=

# --- Provider keys (to create the cloud sandbox) ---

# Daytona. https://app.daytona.io/  (only needed for the Daytona provider)
DAYTONA_API_KEY=

# Vercel Sandbox. https://vercel.com/account/settings/tokens
# (only needed for the Vercel provider; or use VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN instead of the trio)
# VERCEL_TOKEN=
# VERCEL_OIDC_TOKEN=
# VERCEL_TEAM_ID=
# VERCEL_PROJECT_ID=

# ngrok authtoken — tunnels the host tool bridge so REMOTE sandboxes (Vercel,
# Daytona) can call bridged host tools (`tanstackStartRecipe`, `exposePreview`)
# while developing locally. Not needed for docker/local providers.
# https://dashboard.ngrok.com/get-started/your-authtoken
# NGROK_AUTHTOKEN=

# Optional: override the Docker base image (must ship node + npm + git).
# SANDBOX_IMAGE=node:22
